FINAL DEPLOYMENT STEPS (CLIENT SERVER)

Goal
- Run one Docker Compose stack and make these services come up correctly:
  - PostgreSQL
  - HMDM server
  - Cloudflared tunnel
- Public URL should open automatically after docker compose up -d --build.

Prerequisites (on client server)
1. Docker Engine + Docker Compose plugin installed.
2. Domain is on Cloudflare.
3. Cloudflare Tunnel is created in Zero Trust and tunnel token is available.
4. DNS record exists:
   - Type: CNAME
   - Name: brothers-mdm.com
   - Target: _<YOUR_TUNNELID>.cfargotunnel.com
   - Proxy status: Proxied
   - Keep only one CNAME for brothers-mdm.com (no duplicates).

Step 1: Copy project and go to server folder
- Commands:
  cd /path/to/brother-pharmach-mdm/hmdm-server

Step 2: Create environment file
- Commands:
  cp .env.example .env

- Edit .env and set at least:
  DB_PASSWORD=<strong_password>
  HASH_SECRET=<random_long_secret>
  JWT_SECRET=<random_long_secret>
  BASE_URL=https://brothers-mdm.com
  CLOUDFLARED_TUNNEL_TOKEN=eyJhIjoiMTk1ZDcwNWZlMzI5YTQ3MzZkMTczMzQ1MDAwYmI3NGIiLCJ0IjoiNzcwOTQyZGMtOWUwNi00MTAxLWFjMDctYmQwMzBlMTg3MGI5IiwicyI6Ik9UY3paV00zTUdVdE4yTXlZUzAwTkdVekxUazFNamN0WkRabE0yVmhOREExTVRZMSJ9

Step 3: Verify cloudflared ingress config
- File: cloudflared/config.yml
- Required content pattern:
  ingress:
    - hostname: brothers-mdm.com
      service: http://hmdm:8080
    - service: http_status:404

Step 4: Start deployment
- Commands:
  docker compose pull
  docker compose up -d --build

Step 5: Verify services are healthy
- Commands:
  docker compose ps
  docker compose logs --tail=80 hmdm
  docker compose logs --tail=80 cloudflared

- Expected:
  - hmdm-server: healthy
  - cloudflared logs contain "Registered tunnel connection"

Step 6: Verify URL
- Commands:
  curl -I https://brothers-mdm.com

- Expected:
  - HTTP/1.1 200 OK

Auto-start after reboot
- Compose services already use restart: unless-stopped, so containers restart automatically when Docker starts.
- Ensure Docker starts on boot.

Linux server:
- Commands:
  sudo systemctl enable docker
  sudo systemctl start docker

Windows Server (Docker Desktop):
- Enable Docker Desktop start at login and keep existing containers with restart policy.

Operational update command (future releases)
- Commands:
  cd /path/to/brother-pharmach-mdm/hmdm-server
  docker compose up -d --build

Quick troubleshoot
1. If URL shows 530/1033:
   - DNS CNAME target does not match active tunnel ID, or duplicate DNS records exist.
2. If URL shows 503:
   - cloudflared is running without ingress rules or wrong hostname in cloudflared/config.yml.
3. If docker compose fails to start cloudflared:
   - CLOUDFLARED_TUNNEL_TOKEN is missing or invalid in .env.
